Councils are pocketing thousands in change by forcing drivers to overpay for parking because their meters do not accept five or 10 pence coins brought in three years ago
making it impossible for drivers to pay the exact cost of parking
Town hall bosses in Manchester have been accused of pocketing thousands of pounds extra from 240 parking ticket machines in the city because they still do not accept new 5p and 10p pieces
This is because their hourly charges often end in 5p and 10p yet the machines do not accept new five or 10p coins
